{
  "stem": "19210.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were reasonably mixed with the youth groups.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And frankly, we had a hard time to communicate simply because of the language barriers, you know.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the Portuguese group was myself and my brother Abraham, my cousin Nissim Benuiz, B-E-N-U-I-Z, and two other brothers, two sets of other brothers.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and forgive me, I-- Garcia, excuse me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One set of brothers was Garcia, G-A-R-C-I-A, but the other one I cannot remember.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was a very, very-- a handful of Portuguese natives that went to Eretz amongst the-- all the hundreds of immigrants.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so we stuck together pretty much.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Certainly we would try to mingle, but we had the problem.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Some of the-- the people stayed in Portugal very, very short periods of time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Others had stayed a little longer, so they knew a few words in Portuguese.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we would take advantage of that and try to communicate with them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The day passed aboard ship-- I believe it took us about four days from Lisbon to Haifa with that-- including that detour.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But basically, you eat and sleep.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was lot of dancing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The-- these groups would suddenly-- well, the-- the physiognomies had changed drastically when they are in-- when they were in Portugal, as opposed when they were on board ship, because of the simple reason they felt they are going to Eretz.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They are going to the-- to the-- to Palestine, to-- to-- to Israel ultimately.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- and-- and that-- that was the goal, the main goal, you know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the freedom and-- and-- and to be in-- in Eretz was, to them, and not just for the youth, adults as well, was a big difference.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
